<span id="freeTextContainer8305942235603723100">Other than one anecdote about Lincoln&apos;s history litigating on behalf of the railroad and its subsequent debt settlement, the book was an unengaging slog. It was off-putting to read about the ruthless businessmen and deceptive politicians through a lens of heroism amidst the mistreatment of labor, widespread racism, and violence against the Plains Indians.</span>
