<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer5058284365879642838">Stephen Edward Ambrose was an American historian and biographer of U.S. Presidents Dwight Eisenhower and Richard M. Nixon. He received his Ph.D. in 1960 from the University of Wisconsin-Madison. In his final years he faced charges of plagiarism for his books, with subsequent concerns about his research emerging after his death. <br/><br/></span>

</div>
